<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11028a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11028a">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11028a"> 28(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">T</font> plays Will you remember me? / Hom<font color="green">[e]</font> sweet Home to / <font face="wake">I</font> on tra<font color="green">[in]</font>whistle (of <font face="wake">D</font>) </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Unit possibly derives from the <cite>Freeman&apos;s Journal</cite>, issue of 12 June 1924, 8/6: By the Way <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> A Frank Plagiarist. The authorship of &ldquo;Clari, or the Maid of Milan,&rdquo; in which the song &ldquo;Home, Sweet Home,&rdquo; referred to in your columns (writes a correspondent), occurs, has often been questioned. Recent research has revealed evidence that John Howard Payne was not the author of &ldquo;Clari.&rdquo;<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Payne was known in his day as an unscrupulous plagiarist.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Who could expect the sentiment in &ldquo;Home, Sweet Home,&rdquo; from a man like that? </mm> </dd></dl>
